<br>
Bah, the best steak can only be found in Montana.  Anything below that is just an imposter trying to pass themselves off as the &quot;Real Deal&quot;.<br>
<br>
It's been a miserable 5 years for me, living in Texas, trying to find a decent steak anywhere in this state.  But then I look at the cattle and I understand.  No Montana-bred cornmeal-fed Angus stock here boys and girls. It's all bony-ass Brahma's... or even worse, the bastard child perversion called... *shudders*  Brangus.  How dare they!!!!<br>
<br>
But, I agree.  A good steak needs nothing added to make it a mouth-watering experience.  And by all the gods, if I don't have a bit of loverly bloody juice seeping out of the edges, I am sending it back.  Too cooked for this chicita.<br>
<br>
Mmm, steak.  I have got to get back to Big Sky country and get me a decent one.<br>
