<br>
Use a cast iron skillet if possible.  After cooking your marinated and seasoned steak, remove it from the pan.  Add enough red wine to cover the pan.  Scrape everything off of the pan, mixing all that flavor in with the wine.  On low heat, reduce until thicker than a1.  Drizzle over your steak.<br>
<br>
*drools*<br>
<br>
Damn it, now I want a steak. <p>~Wolf/Ssakas/Jr/Whatever</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=caemus>Caemus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/10/03 1:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3835.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: People who don't know how to eat steak...</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Use a cast iron skillet if possible. After cooking your marinated and seasoned steak, remove it from the pan.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
